 "remarks": "This beautiful coastal residence, set on a half-acre, offers stunning views of the Saugatuck Yacht Club and the harbor, stretching to the Long Island Sound. Relax and unwind on the expansive front deck, perfect for soaking in the serene water views. This home features four bedrooms, three and a half baths, two fireplaces, and two decks for waterfront living, with endless expansion possibilities-add a rooftop deck, a second story, or a pool and pool house. The renovated chef&apos;s kitchen, with an induction range and top-line appliances, is brightened by skylights and opens via sliders to the back deck, where a hot tub awaits. The private primary suite, secluded on the second floor, offers lush backyard views, partial lagoon views, and a beautifully appointed primary bathroom. Just a few steps down from the kitchen, a spacious den with a cozy fireplace, a bar, and sliders to the backyard awaits. The lower level offers a large family room, a cedar closet, abundant storage, and direct access to the oversized two-car garage, plus even more storage rooms. Minutes to the train station and I-95, this is a perfect home for water lovers and commuters alike.&quot;",
